Description: RecyclingPerks is a company that gives rewards when users recycle.
Full Description: Recycling Perks, headquartered in Chesapeake, VA is a recycling rewards company that increases recycling participation, volume and operational efficiencies through a turnkey solution that positively impacts residents, businesses, municipalities and haulers.  The program launched in May, 2011 with the City of Chesapeake.  As it stands today Recycling Perks serves seven cities with several more on the horizon.   In its short history, Recycling Perks has been successful in differentiating itself from competition. The program gives communities the opportunity to make an impact on their waste stream through recycling but to also make an impact on local businesses through the use of RFID technology. Using RFID technology and data analysis determinations can be made about which household has recycled, how often, and how that relates to key demographic information.  With these elements in place, Recycling Perks is able to strategically market to areas of low participation and relate use of local rewards partners to the individual a householdâs profile. The benefit of using RFID technology is that it not only allows Recycling Perks to identify areas of improvement, but also allows provides an opportunity to reward, encourage and help to activate others in the community â giving residents ownership in the program.  Recycling Perks targets municipalities and individual haulers looking to increase recycling volume through the use of a recycling rewards program.  Ideal communities for Recycling Perks are (1) in the process of going to single stream from bins, or (2) communities that have a curbside program with stagnant collection metrics.  With the current state of recycling and municipalities doing all they can to get the most out their programs Recycling Perks is well-positioned to be a leader in this area

Description: Theken Spine designs, develops, manufactures, and distributes spinal fixation devices in the United States.
Full Description: Theken Spine designs, develops, manufactures, and distributes spinal fixation devices in the United States. It offers degenerative products, including coral pedicle screw system, a fusion implant system for the correction and stabilization of lumbar or lower region of the spine; and coral friction head screw system for fixation of deformity or degenerative spinal conditions in the thoraco-lumbar spine.  Theken Spine also offers cervical products such as tether anterior cervical plating (ACP) system to provide the stabilization of cervical spine in the case of arthrodesis; atoll cervico-thoracic system to promote fusion for various patient anatomies; and manta ray ACP system that helps surgeons in controlling the plate construct intra-operatively. Moreover, it offers vertebral body (VBR) products that include L-POD and Vu C-POD to allow graft pack inside and around the implant; Vu L-POD PEEK-Optima VBR to match the anatomy of a vertebral endplate; Vu Mesh and Vu e-POD vertebral body replacement systems; and Vu aPOD, an anterior inter vertebral body fusion device.  Further, Theken Spine offers deformity products comprising coral hook formputty, a beta-tricalcium phosphate putty to fill bone voids; trauma/tumor products consisting of X-POD to expand the Theken Spine portfolio with adjustable VBR construct; and bodyform thoracic and thoraco-lumbar fixation system to provide a fixation solution for spine regions from T1-L5, as well as offers synthetic bone substitute products. It markets its products through a network of independent distributors.  Randy Theken founded Theken Spine August 1, 1998, with its headquarters in Akron in Ohio.
